# Update Logging

- Keep project progress in `UPDATE_LOG/` using GitHub-renderable markdown.
- Name entries `YYYY-MM-DD_HHMMSS_short-title.md` so files sort newest-first by timestamp.
- Create a new log entry for each meaningful LLM work session and summarize the user request, work completed, and files changed.
- If the user explicitly describes manual edits or decisions, record them as human updates in the relevant log entry.
- Keep dialog summaries short and simplified.
- Maintain `UPDATE_LOG/README.md` as an index of entries sorted descending by timestamp.
- Do not duplicate unchanged details across many entries; link or summarize instead.
